The Trkr Difference Providing Students With A Powerful Suite of Tools Time Tracking Allowing students to track the different aspects of how they spend their From homework to test Helping to build better study habits and ​ Grade Calculator Putting the grades required in front of students so that they can create goals throughout their course as opposed to at the end​ Calendar Allowing students to make and keep their own schedules, away from the distractions of instructor set notes​ Kanban Board The Kanban board gives students a new way to organize themselves while introducing them to a format that they will see throughout their professional career [COMING SOON!!] Learn More About Trkr Trkr is a software platform which aims to introduce students to the direct relationship between time spent on different aspects of classes and the grades which that time Built by students, for At Trkr we understand the types of challenges those in school Learn more about the benefits of our software below Learn More The Numbers Matter We want to help students do better 1 % Of College Freshman end Up on academic probation 1 % High School Students do Not Graduate Track How you study Worth Use the tool to improve studying habits, and track Previous Next Why it matters Tools to suceed Protect your future while strengthening your Gain access to the tools you need to Use Time Effectively Challenging course loads require solid time management Track your studying breakdown to optimize your GPA matters The average income rate for those who earned a GPA was over $50,000 more than those below a Set Goals Want to hit a target? Frequently Asked Questions - Tally Surgical Skip to content Toggle Navigation Products FAQs Insights About Contact Frequently Asked Questions Frequently Asked Questions Meagan :55 :00 What makes Tally different than other retained sponge solutions? First generation retained sponge prevention technologies, namely barcode and radio frequency technology, have both been commercially available since and , Though both have shown the capacity to be clinically effective in reducing retained surgical sponges in the facilities in which they have been implemented, despite being available for over a decade and a half, the vast majority of hospitals in the have passed on implementing We believe this is due to the limitations of these solutions that are the result of the dated technologies they utilize and the impact on the clinical efficacy, cost and user experience with these Tally is designed to be a reliable, easy to use, low cost and more complete retained sponge Tally is designed to provide an accurate count of surgical sponges faster and easier than competitive retained sponge prevention Accurate – With unique RFID data programmed onto every sponge, Tally helps prevent the inaccurate counts that lead to retained sponges when a manual count alone is relied Fast – The technology powering Tally enables scanning of up to + items per second 7 , dramatically faster than the one at a time process inherent in scanning barcodes and manual Further, unlike barcode technology, Tally’s RFID labels do not require a direct line of sight to be Barcode labels need to be relatively flat and clean and have a direct line of sight between the barcode itself and the barcode reader, whereas Tally is capable of quickly reading numerous sponges relatively simultaneously without requiring the same handling and Easy – In addition to faster, easier scanning and counting, Tally’s proprietary “FIND” feature is designed to help users more quickly locate missing In the event that a count taken prior to surgery does not match a count taken of sponges removed from the patient, Tally’s FIND mode can help guide the user to the exact missing sponge or sponges, helping reconcile the count more Neither barcode technology nor radio frequency technology has this Has Tally been cleared by the FDA? In May of we filed a submission to the FDA regarding Subsequently, the FDA provided us with a formal response letter to our As opposed to clearing Tally through the Premarket Notification Process [510(k)], in the response letter to us the FDA stated that they believe Tally falls within a device classification type and product code that is exempt from the premarket notification requirement More specifically, the FDA stated they believe Tally to fall within CFR under product code LWH and therefore is a Class I type device that is exempt from the premarket notifications [510(k)] Based on this categorization by the FDA, Tally will not require further submissions to seek FDA clearance given the exempt status of the device type and product Does Tally replace manually counting? Tally is designed to be used as an adjunct to a manual count, not as a We combined our deep clinical, development and technology experience, together with extensive input from operating room clinicians, to design Tally to reinforce recommended practices for manual sponge What is the impact of Tally on case time? By improving the ease and speed of accurately counting sponges and providing the ability to more quickly reconcile counts, Tally empowers clinicians to reduce total case When will Tally be available? We are initiating an early adopter program in early that will include the first hospitals using We have filled the spots for hospitals we intend to partner with for this program, however if you are interested in learning more about how your facility can participate please contact We anticipate widespread commercial availability of Tally in Is Tally patent protected? Tally is protected by a broad portfolio of issued and pending patents controlled by Tally Surgical, The Company’s IP portfolio includes multiple patents acquired from third party inventors with extensive backgrounds in RFID and retained sponge How much does Tally cost? We will be disclosing pricing to interested hospitals upon commercial release of Our pricing will reflect our intention to establish Tally as the most compelling retained sponge prevention solution from not just a clinical satisfaction perspective but one of Technology Drive, Suite , Irvine, CA | ©2021 Tally Surgical, | Privacy Policy | Disclaimer Page load link Go to Top   Retained Surgical Sponges - Tally Surgical Skip to content Toggle Navigation Products FAQs Insights About Contact Retained Surgical Sponges Retained Surgical Sponges Meagan :33 :00 A LARGE, PERSISTENT PROBLEM Unintentionally retained surgical sponges are the most common surgical adverse event and lead to significant patient morbidity and cost ramifications 1,2,3 . With Jill’s help, they’ve been able to develop a product with a clean label that they can feed kids (their own included) with a clear The name Sunnie was chosen to convey the feeling sparked by a , nutritious meal: Sunnie meals help kids shine from the inside Sunnie also happens to be the name of Katy’s grandma, who brought sunshine everywhere she Grandma Sunnie (who lived to be !) was utterly devoted to real, unprocessed Katy and Lisette know that she would approve of what they’re feeding the Sunnie In fact, Katy and Lisette really believe that all families deserve to have a little Sunnie in their lives — even (maybe especially) those who can’t afford to buy So, they created the Spread Some Sunnie Learn more here . Collegiate Rugby Championship – Memorial Day Weekend skip navigation National Collegiate Rugby - The Home of College Rugby Collegiate Rugby Championship – Memorial Day Weekend By National Collegiate Rugby , 12 21, 5:00PM EST Share National Collegiate Rugby will host the Collegiate Rugby Championship on Memorial Day Weekend, crowning men’s and women’s national champions in conjunction with a conference representative side The CRC has been the crown jewel of collegiate rugby since , putting the sport on the big stage via national television and major league stadiums and serving as the proving grounds for dozens of future Olympians and pros including Nate Ebner, Madison Hughes and Danny Now owned and operated by NCR, the membership home to more than of college rugby, the CRC is poised for a rebirth as a true national “National Collegiate Rugby is about the player experience, first and foremost, and we are thrilled to welcome the CRC, which has provided an unparalleled stage to so many for so long, to the home of college rugby,” NCR CEO Jeremy Treece All NCR member teams are eligible for selection to A selection committee will be assigned the task of choosing the final men’s teams and women’s teams to compete in CRC May Madness 7’s. All NCR members are eligible for selection to their conferences representative team and all member teams are eligible for selection to the CRC, though they will have to comply with COVID protocols and provide signed consent from school “We are committed to providing the best championship experience possible in , and that begins and ends with We are diligently working with all appropriate parties to assure we provide the safest environment possible for rugby to return to competition in a meaningful way,” NCR Commissioner Pat Clifton Teams with administrative approval to play rugby this spring can apply for consideration here . Features | Remix Buy Features Sign in Web Fundamentals With the rise of JavaScript heavy web sites and client side routing, the React ecosystem has left behind a lot of the fundamental pieces of the Remix brings them back . Things like server rendering, http caching, meta tags, proper status codes–and for Pete s sake document titles! Modern Architecture At the same time, web infrastructure has changed for the CDNs are more advanced, serverless functions give unprecendented scale, browsers have new APIs for preloading resources , bundlers and HTTP 2 change the way we approach code And of course, React s component model is incredible even for plain Remix is built to take advantage of it (Re)Discover the Web Remix teaches you the foundational features of the web and then provides simple APIs for you to take advantage of HTTP Caching We run a website called UNPKG . It serves over billion requests per month without making a dent on our credit card It s possible because of HTTP caching and A trend is to turn to SSG to find performance like this, but then you complicate deployment and give up dynamic content, not to mention UNPKG is simply impossible to build with The result is the same though: a cached document on a You can skip the build bonanza with Remix and keep the performance with our Meta Tags Without server rendered meta tags, your website is simply Meta tags are the reason fancy little website previews show up on social media and text It s also how search engines know how to crawl your site and decide to put you on the first Status Codes and Server Rendering Server rendering provides solid UX advantages and is still the gold standard for SEO, but you might not give much thought to status codes Well, CDNs and search engines certainly For years React apps (even server rendered ones) have been sending s for Not found? No record? Server error? Redirect (!) This hurts your SEO and your CDN Remix sends the right status code, even on client side Data Loading, But Easy Remix makes loading data for a route as simple as it sounds: fetch some data, render Write a server side function to fetch data, Remix does the Centralized Data Loading Remix centralizes data loading on the The initial page is server rendered with data in the markup while automatically fetching in the client as the user navigates That s right, put useEffect back on the Talk directly to your Database Since all data loading is on the server, you can talk directly to your No need to write the function once for the server, and again for the browser (and certainly no screwing around with making things "isomorphic", whatever that means!) Built on Standards Remix also brings the Fetch API to your You can use fetch for network calls and even return real Responses with cache headers and Server side loaders fetch data from anywhere const db = require ( ".. db" ) module . exports = async ( params ) = let user = await db . query ( ` users $ params . userId ` ) return fetch ( ` https: api.github.com users $ user . githubLogin ` ) Data gets passed to your route component export default function UserGithubProfile ( data ) return ( < div < h1 data . name < h1 < Avatar src = data . avatar_url < div ) Nested Routes: The Remix Cheat Code Remix takes advantage of React Router s nested routing paradigm (hat tip Ember) which gives us unique insight into route transitions and Traditional approaches associate resources and UI with This way they can fetch or preload resources for page Unfortunately, when pieces of UI persist you end up refetching stuff the user already has because you don t know enough about the UI to prevent Other approaches try to move resource dependencies all the way down to the component In this case you don t know what resources you need until you render! By then it s too late to do any Layouts, where resources live Your layouts define the data, modules, and styles that a portion of the page needs to Remix routes nested in folders define nested UI and This gives us great insight into what is going to render next when the URL Persisted UI State Remix knows your layouts, so when the page changes you won t lose state in layouts that persist through the URL Best example of this is the scroll position of a sidebar Nested routes only update the changing portion of the Smart Resource Fetching Because Remix knows which layouts are changing and which are not when the URL changes, it only fetches resources that the user doesn t already Less network activity, better UX, simple layout code, everybody s Invoices Projects Customers #10123 #10122 #10121 #10119 #10118 #10117 #10116 Invoice #10121 Details Viewed 10 Sent 09 Created 28 Activity routes invoices.js $id.js http: example.com invoices 10121 activity It s your app, deploy it anywhere Remix is made for the serverless All it needs is a single http handler and a place for static We even ship with packages to help you deploy to some of the most popular Cloud Services, and will continue to add Start shipping be

Faqs - City ERC (929) [email protected] Home Why City ERC Qualifications FAQ Private: Contact Us Home Why City ERC Qualifications FAQ Private: Contact Us Apply Now Home Why City ERC Qualifications FAQ Private: Contact Us Home Why City ERC Qualifications FAQ Private: Contact Us APPLY NOW FAQ’S Frequently Asked Questions Get prompt responses from a friendly, professional and knowledgable support Do I have to repay the ERC? No this is not a loan at This is a tax credit that is When we send in your ERC claim, we request that the refund check be sent directly to How much do you charge? Our costs are calculated based on the credits we will earn for Our free analysis can provide an estimate of how much you can expect to Why would I hire City ERC and not my CPA? You can absolutely hire your CPA however, the ERC is generally claimed on your payroll tax returns and not on your business tax Most CPAs work with business tax Because of this, most CPAs will generally not process this contract unless payroll is completed We at City ERC bridge the gap in utilizing this valuable tax Most of our clients are referred from their CPA because of the ease of a streamlined partnership and value to the clients’ At City ERC, we have decades of experience with payroll, which lets us focus on learning about and making the most of the ERC program for our We have found that clients express difficulty navigating the ERC program, which is where we step in to step up for our In this way, we are able to make the best use of the tax credit program to help your growing Can I benefit from the ERC program if I already have PPP Loans? The Taxpayer Certainty and Disaster Tax Relief (TCDTR) Act of changed the rules for the One of the changes was to make it possible for a company to have PPP Loans and still use the It stated that a business cannot use the same dollar for dollar funds for payroll because that would be considered “double ” When we process your ERC, we account for My revenue increased in do I still qualify for the ERC program? Yes! For , there are three ways to qualify: a drop in income or a full or partial closure of your business due to A full or partial closure, per the IRS, states, “A government authority ordered you to close all or part of your business in or ” This includes, but is not limited to, your operations being limited by business, not being able to travel or hold group Below are some examples of full and or partial closures: Example 1: A restaurant must close or limit the number of people who can dine in (social distancing between tables so every other table must be ) Example 2: A business that relies on customer interactions experiences limitations on the number of customers that can be present at any given Example 3: Because of orders and the cleaning requirements by the state, a business must limit the hours of Example 4: Delays or bottlenecks in the supply chain causes a business to have difficulty meeting production Example 5: Due to rules, a planned business event may have been canceled or limited to the number of I’m a CPA or a payroll company, can I refer my clients to City ERC? Yes, we offer a referral affiliate To learn more, contact us at (929) or at [email protected] Will ERC run out? No, this is not a loan The US Treasury distributes tax refunds therefore, all eligible employers will receive their How do I make my payment to City ERC? We provide two methods of providing payment to City We understand that you may not receive your tax refund check for a few Why am I receiving more in ERC than I paid in taxes? Keep in mind, this program is based on payroll taxes paid, not income If ERC funds are not used for payroll taxes, they are considered an “over deposit” of taxes and the IRS will send a refund As an owner, do my wages and the wages of anyone in my family that I hire count? This depends on the following criteria: The wages of owners with more than % ownership, which is called “Majority Ownership,” do not qualify and neither do the W2 wages of the owner’s immediate family If I am , can I qualify for ERC? If you are not a majority owner (50% or more) then you may be How long does it take to receive my ERC? Generally, from the point of complete document submission, an analysis is completed, and the process can take less than 7 business Upon eligibility determination, we will discuss your payment options then proceed to file your Once your claim is filed, the refund is issued by the Is the ERC taxable? The ERC is not federal income, but you must subtract the amount of credit from any wage expenses that you deduct for tax Please notify your CPA once you receive your Didn’t find an answer to your question? Contact us here . Ready to get started? Data Scientist | cloudomatix DATA DATA WAREHOUSING FILE STORAGE DIGICONNECT RPA Let’s Chat Select Page Data Scientist Data Scientists are the evolution of statistics and math that were commonly referred to Statistician that fused with Computer Scientists power of coding software programs as the models became more non linear and more non parametric and things changed pretty The last mile of this journey is understanding business outcomes and how to use data to steer an organization down the right path of At the moment Data Scientists are hard to come by as they are in high demand and the average tenure is about 9 There is a need to augment that skill set and Data Scientist can do that for The secret to building really good predictive models is not being an expert in any one type of The trick is to try everything, but people are cognitively bound so nobody knows a handful of aaS is a software program that automates the process of building and tuning predictive models so you can find the best Data helps organizations monetize, optimize, automate, and provide actionable insights to their The AI solution inside of Data Scientist automates some task that would normally require human Machine Learning Models AI Prediction Models Platform incorporates modeling techniques from data scientists to automatically produce dozens of machine learning models with the click of a This enables anyone, regardless of data science expertise, to build practical machine learning models that have tangible effects on a business’s bottom It runs what we call “model blueprints,” that contain the machine learning algorithm in addition to a combination of data , feature engineering, and Model blueprints result in more relevant insights into your data, allowing you to make better decisions that yield tangible business Additionally, the platform’s guardrails and best practices from the minds of some of the best data scientists ensure that your models are as accurate and practical as It also has tools to increase the interpretability of machine learning models it creates, allowing users to more easily communicate insights from model outcomes to the ultimate regarding whether or not those models are deployed into What are Prediction Explanations in Machine Learning? Traditionally, machine learning models have not included insight into why or how they arrived at an This makes it difficult to objectively explain the decisions made and actions taken based on these Prediction Explanations avoid the “black box” syndrome by describing which characteristics, or feature variables, have the greatest impact on a model’s Why are Prediction Explanations Important for Machine Learning? When the reasons behind a model’s outcomes are as important as the outcomes themselves, Prediction Explanations can uncover the factors that most contribute to those For example, banks using models to determine whether or not they should approve a loan can use Prediction Explanations to gain insight into why an application was accepted or With that insight they can develop models that comply with regulations, easily explain model outcomes to stakeholders, and identify factors to help focus their business Prediction Explanations AI Prediction Explanations allow you to calculate the impact of a configurable number of features (the “reasons”) for each outcome your model Once calculated, you can preview the top explanations or download the full Each explanation is a feature from the dataset intrinsic pontine glioma (DIPG) Malignant brain tumors account for % of childhood cancer deaths each Diffuse intrinsic pontine glioma (DIPG), affecting an estimated children and a similar number of adults in the United States per DIPG is one of the most deadly cancers of any The diagnosis of DIPG is typically made using clinical symptoms and magnetic resonance (MR) Because of the location of the tumors in the brainstem, diagnostic biopsies require special neurosurgical expertise and equipment only available in a few specialized Children with DIPG often die within one year from diagnosis and this prognosis has not changed significantly in three Defining the enemy Patients and parents with their physician advocates are challenging the status quo by participating in DIPG The recent availability of tissue from stereotactic biopsies and rapid autopsies has led to studies that show scientists what causes DIPG and what makes it One important discovery was the common occurrence of missense mutations the Histone 3 genes ( H3F3A K27M) and ( HIST1H3B C K27M). These mutations are present in most DIPGs and represent an early tumorigenic event . The World Health Organization (WHO) now classifies DIPG and midline gliomas with these mutations together as a distinct pathologic group known as diffuse midline glioma, H3K27 mutant . These mutations appear to set the stage for acquiring additional driver Each tumor may have a unique set of driver mutations that cause the tumor cells to divide and invade normal brain Knowing a tumor’s driver mutations is an important step in selecting treatments that may halt tumor growth . Diagnosis of H3K27M tumors with liquid biopsy A preliminary study performed in the Nazarian laboratory at Children’s Research Institute at Children’s National Health System evaluated the potential benefit of liquid biopsy for diagnosis of diffuse midline 20 (90%) of children with H3K27M mutant tumors had detectable circulating tumor DNA (ctDNA) in plasma suggesting that plasma testing may be used to confirm the This is important as documentation of the pathology of the brainstem mass is an important entry requirement for a number of clinical Because H3K27M occurs in diffuse midline glioma and is extremely rare in other cancers, detection of H3K27M in ctDNA can be used in place of tissue Can H3K27M monitoring help determine if a treatment is working? Interestingly, in the study described above, the blood test results were quantitative and correlated with tumor volume measured by MR The amount of tumor DNA in plasma decreased when the tumor was responding to therapy, and increased when tumors regrew after Imagine not having to wait several months to know if a drug is working or Finding a better and more sensitive way to know that the drug is or isn’t killing tumor cells will help doctors find the best treatment for each Moving liquid biopsy into standard of care ResourcePath partnered with Nazarian’s research laboratory and Ahura Biologics to bring liquid biopsy for diffuse midline glioma into the clinical laboratory ResourcePath took the valuable information learned by Nazarian’s group and others to update and optimize a ddPCR assay to detect minute amounts of tumor DNA in the Initial testing confirmed that tumor DNA harboring H3K27M mutations is detectable in blood in about % of In addition, in a small pilot study with Oncoceutics, Inc , we learned that the quantity of tumor DNA in blood corresponds with response to treatment and size of the tumor as measured by MR Next steps Over the next several months we will be working with Fred Kramer and Diana at the Public Health Research Institute at Rutgers University to maximize the sensitivity of our test and expand the spectrum of mutations the test can detect to include H3F3A G34R V and BRAF V600E . deciding which candidates will progress to the next stage and who will fall at the first We are empowering people to communicate themselves confidently and capture the opportunities they are striving for in this brave new Get Started Interview prep Capture About a year ago, one of our applied to their dream MBA It was a long slog hitting that GMAT score, writing essays, collecting transcripts and preparing for Eventually, they were accepted into prestigious business schools such as Stanford GSB and MIT Unfortunately lack of preparation for the video assessments almost stole these opportunities Today the stakes are even Voomer uses cutting edge artificial intelligence processing inspired by MIT Media Lab research to ensure that applicants get the best, unbiased video interview prep in the shortest amount of time Getting into a dream school can change your life for the better in a multitude of ways - we want to help you get Get Started AI Artificial intelligence enhanced video analysis Natural Language Object Vocal Emotion All fancy terms for essentially the same thing - listening to what you say and how you say Voomer uses AI to break things down into their individual parts, figure out what can be improved and then tell you how to get From the trivial, such as camera angle, to the complex, such as building up your inner Get Started Science Scientifically proven methods When building Voomer, we stayed close to our MIT roots and utilize artificial intelligence algorithms only on issues that had a solid causal relationship with better video interview and assessment Eye contact , body language , and vocal tone are all key components when communicating with another person on a video interview and measuring those elements are the first things that Voomer does with your video Get Started Optimized Optimized for native and English speakers MBA programs always look to build very geographically diverse cohorts , since that adds to the MBA That obviously means that for many applicants, English is not their first According to the Washington Post , despite competitive applicants having very good command of the English language, accents can sometimes throw off automated analysis algorithms and return results that are not necessarily reflective of Voomer is built to enable you to understand and accommodate your accent, pulling on a broad range of definitions when interpreting the words you use when responding to an interview This allows our artificial intelligence algorithms to give you feedback that is not led astray by the fact that you might not be a native English Get Started Voomer Twitter icon YouTube icon Facebook icon Support Privacy Policy | Terms of Service | Disclaimer ©2020 All Rights Create Account Already have an account? WeHealth Technology Platform for Public Health Solutions Smartphone App Platform EN Express Partners Public Health Forum Science of Pandemic Tech Services About Blog Contact Platform for Public Health Our technology solution includes three components: a mobile app, a administrative portal, and verification and key Implementation support is provided by our services Interoperable WeHealth builds apps from the Covid Watch open source codebase, built on the Exposure Notification (GAEN) protocol, with production API access for multiple jurisdictions in and outside of the Efficient Provides a complete feedback loop from public health authorities to individuals, offering details about the risk of exposure so that the user can make an informed decision about precautions and next Proven Our platform has gone through rigorous testing, from signal strength calibration to of an original dynamic risk scoring App Our mobile app is based on Covid Watch and uses the Google Apple Exposure Notification (GAEN) APIs to harness anonymous, temporary, Bluetooth Low Energy (BLE) signals to infer physical distance between two mobile Our app was one of the first exposure notification apps built using the GAEN APIs to be piloted in the United States and we continue to collaborate with Apple and Google to ensure our app meets their joint requirements including interoperability between Android and iOS GAEN is quickly becoming the “gold standard” in many countries for the development of , apps which we are committed to The mobile app interface can be customized with branding specific to your region and the public health authority responsible for combating The code is open source . Learn More Portal The Portal enables public health officials to perform administrative functions concerning: Keeping track of contact tracing personnel who generate security codes Secure retrieval of diagnostic verification codes for users who tested positive Branding or customization to suit regional needs Customization of mobile messaging, language or other localization Calibration of signal strength and other factors contributing to risk scoring The Portal is integrated regionally so that app users receive relevant local health Verification and Key Servers The functions of the WeHealth Platform are split over two distinct server components: the Verification Server and the Key These are independent, projects currently developed and maintained by Google as part of their larger contribution to the GAEN WeHealth hosts its own instances of the Verification Server and Key Server as part of our overall product offering, integrated with the App and the Our platform is fully compatible with APHL national key servers and verification The Verification Server It provides and validates cryptographically secure numeric codes intended for verifying The Covid Watch Portal accesses this Verification Server to provision verification codes to authorized public health officials (i.e. case investigators, clinicians or other health professionals), who then distribute them to individuals for entry into the Covid Watch The app communicates directly with the Verification Server to validate the authenticity and expiration status of a code, and to exchange it for a certificate allowing secure transmission of a contact exposure key to the Key The Key Server It is a separate piece of infrastructure with which the App communicates It allows uploading of the temporary exposure key data which the App shares via Bluetooth during the period surrounding a verified positive diagnosis (and authorized by a valid code from the Verification Server). The Key Server also packages and signs all newly uploaded key data each day and makes it available for download by the App This allows the App to compare exposure keys to key data that the App previously captured to determine if the user had a potential exposure–which would result in a local Exposure Verification Code Delivery WeHealth is developing new ways to speed up the delivery of verification codes by integrating code delivery with existing systems to make the process easier for health care professionals and patients For example, via API access to the verification servers, our partners can generate and display a code directly in their patient portal UI alongside positive test We are also partnering directly with labs, such as Paradigm to offer verification codes with About Blog Privacy Policy Copyright WeHealth Solutions, a Public Benefit   The Science of Pandemic Technology: Seminar Series Solutions Smartphone App Platform EN Express Partners Public Health Forum Science of Pandemic Tech Services About Blog Contact The Science of Pandemic Technology Seminar Series is dedicated to showcasing the latest and best available scientific research to inform digital health innovation for COVID This series is by WeHealth and the Big Data Institute at the University of Sign up to learn more about upcoming events and join the Science of Pandemic Technology

This chapter is supported by CodeVA, a statewide CS advocacy organization, Microsoft, the Institute for Advanced Learning and Research, and Broadband (MBC).
